  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [x] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (a5171a4 2023-12-24T00:17:25.574824499Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\nWindows\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen try to compile file that have the encode `UTF-8 with BOM' will crash (btw i use WSL2)\r\n```\r\nforge build\r\n[⠒] Compiling...\r\n[⠢] Compiling 1 files with 0.8.23\r\n[⠆] Solc 0.8.23 finished in 5.89ms\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  byte index 5 is not a char boundary; it is inside '\\u{feff}' (bytes 4..7) of `1 | // SPDX-License-Identifier: GPL-3.0`\r\nLocation: /home/runner/.cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-6f17d22bba15001f/foundry-compilers-0.1.1/src/artifacts/mod.rs:2085\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe example file that case the problem: (json ext so i can upload it here)\r\n[Test.json](https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/files/13763065/Test.json)\r\n",
